OL,7,FMr Dry said a relative travelling in
OL,8,Fthe car in front of Mr Hain's had
OL,9,Fnoticed Rutherford's car travelling in
OL,10,Fthe opposite direction and commented
OL,11,Fabout the speed.
OL,13,FMr Dry added: "Given the speed of the
OL,14,Fdefendant he was concerned for the
OL,15,Fsafety of second car, being driven by
OL,16,Fhis uncle David."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G7/15
