OL,5,Cdinner'
OL,7,F"It was so traumatic to wake up from
OL,8,Fbeing unconscious and realising that
OL,9,Fmy husband was no longer in the
OL,10,Fdriving seat and turning around to see
OL,11,Fmy daughter slumped in the back with
OL,12,Fblood coming from her head and over
OL,13,Fher face.
OL,15,F"I was terrified but was able to exit
OL,16,Fthe car and was taken to hospital by
OL,17,Fambulance. I spent 12 days in the
OL,18,Ftrauma ward and was unable to walk due
OL,19,Fto the concussion. It was a very
OL,20,Fpainful time both emotionally and
OL,21,Fphysically.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G11/15
