OL,4,Cinjured three as he sped home 'for
OL,5,Cdinner'
OL,7,F"My husband and daughter were taken to
OL,8,Fintensive care with extensive
OL,9,Finjuries. Meg had broken bones in her
OL,10,Flegs and pelvis but the most worrying
OL,11,Fthing was the head injury she
OL,12,Fsustained.
OL,14,F"Both were put into comas so that the
OL,15,Fmedics could work on the me and I was
OL,16,Funable to speak to David again as he
OL,17,Fnever recovered from his injuries.
OL,18,FThey turned off his life support on
OL,19,FOctober 3 and he passed away. I was
OL,20,Fdevestated as I lost my soulmate and
OL,21,Fhusband of 27 years."
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}       G12/15
